## Submit a task

```bash
curl https://llm.bytespike.ai/v1/tasks/submit \
  -H "x-api-key: $BYTESPIKE_API_KEY" \
  -H "content-type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "model": "{/* model_id */}",
    "prompt": "A drone shot tracking a yellow cab through Times Square at golden hour.",
    "duration_seconds": 5,
    "resolution": "{/* 720p / 1080p */}"
  }'
```

### Body parameters

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `model` | string | yes | — | `{/* model_id */}` |
| `prompt` | string | yes | — | Text prompt. {/* "CJK accepted" / "English-only" */} |
| `duration_seconds` | integer | yes | — | Range: {/* 1-10 */}. Each second billed at {/* $X/s */}. |
| `resolution` | string | no | {/* 720p */} | Supported: {/* "720p, 1080p" */} |
| `aspect_ratio` | string | no | `16:9` | Supported: {/* "16:9, 9:16, 1:1" */} |
| `seed` | integer | no | — | Reproducibility. |
| `image_init` | string | no | — | {/* URL of init image for image-to-video — delete if not supported */} |
| `motion_intensity` | string | no | {/* medium */} | {/* e.g. "low / medium / high" — delete if not applicable */} |
| `{/* model-specific */} ` | {/* type */} | no | — | {/* e.g. `style_preset` for some models */} |

### Submit response

```json
{
  "task_id": "task_{/* … */}",
  "status": "queued",
  "estimated_credits": {/* e.g. 0.42 */},
  "submitted_at": "{/* ISO-8601 */}"
}
```

The estimated credits land **before** any GPU work starts — call
[`tasks/cancel`](/api-reference/utility/tasks-cancel) before status flips
to `running` for a free abort. After `running`, partial seconds are
billed.

## Poll for completion

```bash
curl "https://llm.bytespike.ai/v1/tasks/query?task_id=task_{/* … */}" \
  -H "x-api-key: $BYTESPIKE_API_KEY"
```

### Status transitions

```
queued → running → completed   (happy path)
queued → cancelled             (free, cancel before running)
queued → running → cancelled   (partial-billed, partial result)
queued → running → failed      (free, see error envelope)
```

### Completed response

```json
{
  "task_id": "task_{/* … */}",
  "status": "completed",
  "result": {
    "video_url": "https://cdn.bytespike.ai/vid/{/* … */}",
    "duration_seconds": 5,
    "resolution": "{/* 1080p */}",
    "aspect_ratio": "16:9"
  },
  "credits": {/* e.g. 0.42 */},
  "completed_at": "{/* ISO-8601 */}"
}
```

Video URLs are pre-signed, valid for **24 hours**. Download and rehost
if you need long-term storage.

### Recommended polling cadence

| Phase | Cadence |
|---|---|
| First 60s | Every 2s |
| 60s – 180s | Every 5s |
| Past 180s | Every 10s |

The query endpoint is **free**.

## Code examples

<CodeGroup>

```bash cURL
# Submit
curl https://llm.bytespike.ai/v1/tasks/submit \
  -H "x-api-key: $BYTESPIKE_API_KEY" \
  -H "content-type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "model": "{/* model_id */}",
    "prompt": "A drone shot tracking a yellow cab through Times Square at golden hour.",
    "duration_seconds": 5,
    "resolution": "{/* 1080p */}"
  }'

# Poll
curl "https://llm.bytespike.ai/v1/tasks/query?task_id=task_{/* … */}" \
  -H "x-api-key: $BYTESPIKE_API_KEY"
```

```python Python
import time
import requests

API = "https://llm.bytespike.ai/v1"
HEADERS = {"x-api-key": "$BYTESPIKE_API_KEY"}

# 1. Submit
submit = requests.post(
    f"{API}/tasks/submit",
    headers=HEADERS,
    json={
        "model": "{/* model_id */}",
        "prompt": "A drone shot tracking a yellow cab through Times Square at golden hour.",
        "duration_seconds": 5,
        "resolution": "{/* 1080p */}",
    },
).json()
task_id = submit["task_id"]

# 2. Poll
while True:
    r = requests.get(f"{API}/tasks/query", params={"task_id": task_id}, headers=HEADERS).json()
    if r["status"] == "completed":
        print(r["result"]["video_url"])
        break
    if r["status"] in ("failed", "cancelled"):
        raise RuntimeError(r)
    time.sleep(2)
```

```javascript Node
const API = "https://llm.bytespike.ai/v1"
const headers = {
  "x-api-key": process.env.BYTESPIKE_API_KEY,
  "content-type": "application/json",
}

// 1. Submit
const submitRes = await fetch(`${API}/tasks/submit`, {
  method: "POST",
  headers,
  body: JSON.stringify({
    model: "{/* model_id */}",
    prompt:
      "A drone shot tracking a yellow cab through Times Square at golden hour.",
    duration_seconds: 5,
    resolution: "{/* 1080p */}",
  }),
})
const { task_id } = await submitRes.json()

// 2. Poll
while (true) {
  const r = await fetch(`${API}/tasks/query?task_id=${task_id}`, { headers })
  const body = await r.json()
  if (body.status === "completed") {
    console.log(body.result.video_url)
    break
  }
  if (body.status === "failed" || body.status === "cancelled") {
    throw new Error(JSON.stringify(body))
  }
  await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, 2000))
}
```

</CodeGroup>

## Errors

| Code | Trigger | Billed? |
|---|---|---|
| 400 | Body validation (duration out of range, resolution unsupported) | No |
| 401 | Missing / revoked key | No |
| 402 | Wallet exhausted (estimated credits exceed balance) | No |
| 403 | Scope denied / IP not allowlisted | No |
| 413 | Prompt or init image too large | No |
| 422 | Param not supported by this model | No |
| 429 | Rate-limited | No |
| 451 | Prompt blocked by upstream safety filter | No |
| 5xx | Upstream provider issue | No (auto-retry envelope) |

The only billable failure: cancelling a task after it transitions to
`running`. Partial GPU seconds rendered are charged. Cancel during
`queued` to abort for free.

See [Error Handling](/concepts/error-handling) for the full enum.

